      - **LESSON-016 Draft-and-Prove Rule (FID-004-system / FID-004r2 / FID-005-feature / FID-005r2 drift self-correction)** — *Codified 2026-07-13 after Spencer's drift critique; strengthened 2026-07-13 after LESSON-016 self-audit revealed a pasteback-without-claim-diff residual gap.* Root cause of the rejected FIDs: paraphrased citations of savant-orig filesystem evidence (line numbers + claimed code behavior) without re-verification pasteback. **`src/app/chat/page.tsx:40-49` self-documents the failure**: an in-tree comment admits "FID-005r2 reverted on 2026-07-13 — the YAML-frontmatter schema was a hallucination." **Three required elements per cited claim going forward (pasteback survives; two new layered elements added):** **(1) Pasteback** — every filesystem or code-behavior claim must include either (a) a fenced `grep -rn <symbol> <path>` raw paste with line numbers, or (b) a 3+ line `sed -n '<start>,<end>p' <file>` excerpt that matches the description; **(2) Claim-equivalence self-check** — the pasteback must be IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWED BY a one-line direct restatement of the FIDO's interpretation of that pasteback, plus an explicit equivalence assertion. Pasteback alone proves what the file says; the self-check proves that the FIDO's interpretation matches reality (the precise gap that produced the r2 YAML-frontmatter hallucination); **(3) Loop-0 diff loop-line** — in the FIDO's Perfection Loop §Loop-0 (FID-doc convergence) section, include one explicit `Diff: claim vs pasteback — <verdict>` line per cited claim, `<verdict>` ∈ {PASS, PARTIAL, FAIL}; FAIL auto-rejects advance past `analyzed`, PARTIAL keeps the existing `[UNVERIFIED-FID-CITE]` marker until pasteback parity is achieved, PASS clears the marker. **Pre-authorship `find` gate deferred to tooling** — companion check `find <savant-orig-root> -name '<cited-file>'` would catch pasteback-able files that don't exist, but it requires either a pre-commit hook or a basher-orchestrated check; out of LESSON-016 scope. **Combined governance:** paraphrased citations auto-classify `[UNVERIFIED-FID-CITE]`; the FIDO cannot advance past `analyzed` until pasteback + claim-equivalence self-check + Loop-0 PASS verdict all land. Author + reviewer remain separate subagent identities (FID-151 cross-agent rule, reinforced). All 4 drift FIDs archived to `dev/fids/archive/` with `[DRIFT-REJECTED]` filename marker per ECHO §FID Auto-Archive + the audit-trail preservation discipline this lesson encodes.
      
